sequenceDiagram
    participant R as Requester
    participant M as Manager
    participant P as Procurement
    participant V as Vendor
    participant F as Finance

    R->>M: Submit purchase request
    M-->>R: PR approved
    M->>P: Forward approved PR
    P->>V: Issue Purchase Order
    V-->>P: Order confirmation
    V->>F: Submit invoice
    F->>F: 3-way match verification

    %% ⚡ CHANGED SECTION
    alt 3-way match successful
        F-->>V: Payment processed (NET30)
    else 3-way match failed - discrepancy found
        F-->>P: Notify discrepancy (PO/Invoice/Receipt mismatch)
        P->>V: Request invoice correction / clarification
        V-->>P: Submit revised invoice or documentation
        P->>F: Forward corrected documents
        F->>F: Re-verify 3-way match
        F-->>V: Payment processed (NET30)
    end
    %% ⚡ END CHANGED SECTION

%% ========================================================
%% CLAUDE'S CHANGE INTERPRETATION
%% ========================================================
%% OBJECTIVE: Ensure invoice discrepancies are formally resolved before payment, preventing financial losses from mismatched purchase orders, receipts, and invoices.
%%
%% EXPLANATION:
%% Replaced the unconditional payment step with an alt/else block: when the 3-way match succeeds, payment proceeds normally; when it fails, Finance notifies Procurement of the discrepancy, Procurement coordinates with the Vendor to obtain corrected documentation, and Finance re-verifies before releasing payment.
%% ========================================================
